OL,6,FMs Metcalfe said "there was a clear
OL,7,Fabuse of power," and that Whiting's
OL,8,Ffather was "clearly a highly
OL,9,Fvulnerable individual" at the time.
OL,11,FWhiting, 49, of Rokeby Park, admitted
OL,12,Ffraud.
OL,14,FShe was given a two year prison
OL,15,Fsentence, suspended for two years, and
OL,16,F240 hours' unpaid work.
